Function Reference/wp category checklist « WordPress Codex
-----------

Output an unordered list of checkbox `<input>` elements labelled with
category names.

Usage
-----

` <?php   wp_category_checklist( $post_id, $descendants_and_self, $selected_cats,         $popular_cats, $walker, $checked_ontop);?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$post_id` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required or optional??*) Mark categories associated with this post
    as checked. `$selected_cats` must not be an array.
    Default: 0

 `$descendants_and_self` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*??*) ID of the category to output along with its descendents.
    Default: 0

 `$selected_cats` 
:   ([*boolean|array*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean.7Carray "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*??*) List of categories to mark as checked.
    Default: false

 `$popular_cats` 
:   ([*boolean|array*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean.7Carray "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*??*) Override the list of categories that receive the
    "popular-category" class.
    Default: false

 `$walker` 
:   ([*object*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Object "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*??*) Walker object to use to build the output.
    Default: null

 `$checked_ontop` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*??*) Move checked items out of the hierarchy and to the top of the
    list.
    Default: true

Examples
--------

Changelog
---------

Since 2.5.1

Source File
-----------

`wp_category_checklist()` is located in
`wp-admin/includes/template.php`.

